content.detailedDescription:
Traveling east on u.S. rt.30 i noticed 3 lights in a stretched triangle shape due east from my position at the intersection of rt.30 and wolf road in mokena, il. after seeing them i asked my brother, who was traveling with me, if he had any idea what they were. as we are both very usedto the presence of commercial aircraft, as these lights had nothing in common with commercial aircraft, we ruled that possibility out.

  the lights seemed to be stationary as related to distance from my self,(approximately 8 miles?) but their positions did change quite a bit. as i traveled east along rt.30 at approximately 40mph i was unable to get closer to them. i assume they were travelling about the same rate of speed as myself. the lights were very low in the sky, sometimes below the tree line, but mostly just above the tree line. the lights were continuously flashing the colors of white, yellow, gold, and occasionally red. at times the flashing was in unison.

  about one mile east of us rt45(lagrange rd.) i dropped my brother of at his house. we spent about 5-7 minuites inside. when returning to the outside, we noticed the lights were still there. at that point i decided to try following them further, hoping for a better vantage point. when i got roughly half a mile from harlem ave., i noticed a fourth light moving toward the others. when i reached harlem ave. the fourth light had merged with one of the original three. i thought it would go past, but it never did. it just merged.

  to say the lights were in a triangular shape would be accurate, however the triangle shape was constantly changing. the motions were almost fluid like.

  at the intersection of us.30 and ridgeland ave. (now in cook county) i stopped to take a photograph with my cell phone. i took a single photo, but i don't think it turned out well. i have attached the photo. the lights are barely visible in the white box
content.summary: Lights from 2004 tinley park sighting seem to have re-appeared

content.detailedDescription:
A doctor that i work with at local hospital reported this case to me... 

he reports that he was east-bound on interstate 40 near weatherford, ok near dark, that would have been about 8 p.M. at that time. he stated this incident happened about 6 weeks ago but he is just now wanting to come forward and report it to someone.

he reported seeing a bright white streak of light that he said reminded him of the shuttle debris footage. he saw pieces of the object fall off and away from the object. 

he described seeing the object for what he described as "5 degrees across the sky" going from the south to the north. 

he reported that it took about 5 minutes for the object to cross the sky, also, he reported people parking along the interstate and getting out of their cars -looking at this object. 

he wanted to know if anyone else had seen this object, and asked me to check. what i found unusual was the movement he reported.

i had asked him to describe the movement of the object and he described the streak to go in "spurts" moving a bit and then stopping. he said he had never seen a object do that in the sky before. 

he is a professional physician that i've personally known and worked with for over 19 years. i believe he saw something. he did not want to report this further than to report it to mufon. i am relaying his report.

thanks!

jim hickman
mufon research specialist
content.summary: Streek of lights across the sky

content.detailedDescription:
I was asleep in my bed in orr, minnesota on pelican lake's south shore. the light was so bright that it came thru the room darkening curtains and woke me. i couldn't figure out what it was that woke me for the first few moments,  as i said, i had been asleep. i got out of bed and walked to the window to see what was making the light, and all i could see was bright light.  everything in the woods was lit up brightly.  i could not see a source for the light.  i was going to wake my husband and the light went out.  there was no explanation.
the following morning, i mentioned this to my husband.  neither of us could come up with an explanation.  later that day, my husband was talking with a neighbor who lives about a mile away, and to our surprise, he experienced a similar ordeal.  he however, was awake when he saw the unexplaned light.
content.summary: Very bright light - no noise

content.detailedDescription: Approximately 1930 as we were headed west on hwy 6 into hico, my wife and i saw two groups of yellow lights in the nw approximately 40 degrees above the horizon.  there were several lights in each group in a oval or circle.  for less than a minute the trees obscured our view but it seemed that they were randomly flashing.  after clearing the trees the lights were gone but we noticed the lights of 2 high flying aircraft headed toward ft worth.
content.summary: Two groups of yellow lights

content.detailedDescription: On saturday, december 12th at around 9:30am i was outside on my back porch in bayside, queens.  my back porch faces north. i was a crisp beautiful morning, blue skies and not a cloud to be seen.  at this time i was on a cordless phone speaking to my friend.  while talking i looked to the north east and saw about 12-15 individual "white balls" in the shape of a triangle.  i did not get the sense it was one object.  they did not move, they were stationary.  i told my friend on the phone "i have to put the phone down". i had a pair of binoculars on the porch. as i grabbed them i kept my eye fixed on the triangle shape.  the objects started to fade and then finally disappeared. about 5 seconds after they disappeared, the faded back into view but this time the "white balls" were shaped like a boomerang.  the binoculars were already in my hand from my first attempt to look at them. i put them to my face and looked...I saw nothing..Pulled the binocular away from my face...The objects were gone.  again both shapes were stationary between fades. the whole experience lasted maybe 15-20 seconds. it was a very strange experience i am curious if anything else was reported in the area as well.
content.summary: Collective white stationary "balls" during daytime hours

content.detailedDescription:
We were having a christmas drinks party at home when we looked outside and saw this thing. it didn't appear to be reflective but was lit up a bt because of the moon on it.

i think it might be a warship, here from another planet to assess our capitol.

i only noticed it when my wife saw it and her mouth fell open. i only lost sight of it as it started getting smaller, i think heading towards lafayette square. i thought it was just something like that thing how those people said their kid was in it, starting a manhunt but i knew it wasn't from ameica when it lit up on the back and started moving. i felt pretty freaked about it when it was gone.

content.detailedDescription: My friend picked me up from the airport and i was telling him about aliens and ufos because i have been researching them lately. we got back to his house and our other friend came over to visit. my buddy who picked me up mentioned to us that there was two bright lights off in the distance up in the sky that he has never seen before out the same window he looks out every night. we didnt even really pay attention to him to come and have a look. about half and hour passed by and he mentioned it to us again that the lights were still there in the same spot and we went to have a look out the window, we saw two sphere  bright orange orb shaped objects up in the sky, it looking like fire burning off in the distance but it was clearly above the ground level up in the sky. i got really excited and told them ive seen the orange orb type ufo on you tube and that we witnessed a real ufo or something unexplainable. it felt really erry a weird feeling of belief. my buddy who first saw them went to get some binoculars and a camera. so it was me and my other friend looking out the window then out of no where one of the orange orbs just vanished, it was gone, just disappeared. it tripped us right out. so we went outside to look from another view, and i was yelling at my other friend to hurry up with the camera. we went outside and it was just us two who saw the first one vanish. i kid u not as soon as my buddy came outside with the camera the other orange orb vanished and dissapeared like the other one did. the objects did not move they were just sitting in the same position until they vanished. me or him have not seen anything else in that same area out the window since. after it happened i called one of my friends and was telling him about it and he said that a few months earlier around the same area my friend lives that he and a few others saw a similar sighting like that i described.
content.summary: Two orange orbs looked as if on fire up in the sky in the distance!

content.detailedDescription:
on december 15, 2009 at 4:49pm i saw a large triangular ufo flying over las vegas.
      i was driving north on hualapi rd. while stopped at the traffic light on hualapi and alta dr. i saw what looked like a "flying saucer" with revolving lights in the distance over the mountains to the northwest of my car. almost immediately it was close enough to see that it was triangular in shape with flashing lights. as it descended i believe that the lights stopped flashing and it looked exactly like the often broadcast video of the "phoenix lights" except that it was not completely dark outside yet here like it was in phoenix when that video was taken. i have heard that the "phoenix lights" was caused by  military flairs, so i was looking for smoke coming from the lights and there was none. i also noticed that it was no longer descending and just hovering so i ruled out flairs. this entire part of the sighting from the time i first noticed it until i concluded that it was just hovering took probably no more than 20 seconds, if that. and then "poof" it was gone. the traffic light changed, i continued north on hualapai and there it was again outside my driver's side window, but only for a second and then "poof" it was once again ahead of my car but a bit farther east than the first time i saw it. i pulled my car over to the right lane, stopped, put on my hazard lights, grabbed my i-phone and tried to take a picture of it. it vanished once again right as i clicked the camera and i only got the fading of the last light and you have to look really hard to even see that. immediately, it was far away in the northwest sky, much lower than my first sighting. i decided to chase it down to get a good photo of it. i had to look down to turn off my hazard lights and when  i looked back up at where it had been it was gone. i drove up to the highest place i could think of with a good view of the city and waited about a half hour but i never saw it again.
content.summary: On december 15, 2009 at 4:49pm i saw a triangle shaped ufo flying over las vegas.

content.detailedDescription: My family and i were facing south on s 6th street, waiting to turn west onto the south loop. as we were waiting to turn onto the loop, i noticed two columns of bright amber lights hovering beneath two aircraft. there were approximately 4 huge amber lights in each column. just as quickly as i had noticed the lights, they faded from the top down in less than a second or two. the aircraft continued flying in what appeared to be an eastern direction. the lights and aircraft were midway up in the sky. i see a lot of small private planes around this area. judging by their speed and the lights on these aircraft i would say they were small private planes. the lights faded so quickly after noticing them that my wife didn't even have a chance to see them. the lights looked like a set of stadium lights turned at a 90 degree angle, except much bigger. i would guess that the lights were as big as a quarter at arms length.
content.summary: Amber lights briefly iluminated below two aircraft

content.detailedDescription:
I left my office at around 6:10 pm. i am about 3 miles from home. as i was driving down the main street i notice three lights in the sky. the sky is typical heavy traffic area for planes heading to the st. louis airport, which is approximately 27 miles east of this occurrence.

what caught my eye was these lights were spread apart quite a bit, but consistent in distance. they were in a straight line and blinking in sequential order (1-2-3, etc.) i thought that perhaps that what i was seeing was a tower of some sort that i didn���t notice before because it would be abnormal to see places flying in this formation. plus, these planes were not headed towards the airport, nor were they, from my position; coming from the direction of the main airport. that���s why i thought they could be tower lights that warn low flying planes at night. but, that was not the case.

as i continued down the main road (which is a busy road) i stretched to see them out my front and passenger window. i don���t ever recall seeing lights like this as a steady fixture, so i was trying to think of what it could be. once i lost sight of the lights, since they were in my blind spot, i continued on and entered into my neighborhood. once i am in my neighborhood i have to back track to get to my home. that���s when i saw the lights again. it was clear that it was not a tower as they appeared to be moving west. 

i ran in the house, asked my husband to go outside in the back yard and tell me what that is in the sky. i didn���t even turn off my car or park it in the garage as i wanted him to see this and explain what it was that i was seeing before it was out of our sight line. 

he is a 23-year military veteran and very familiar with various military air craft. looking through the bare trees in our yard, he said he didn���t know, but was sure that military planes wouldn���t fly in such as straight line with lights that blinked sequentially. 

i went in and grabbed the camera and went out front of the house to see if i could get a better view. a house was blocking the view, so we got in the car. we figured we could get to an open space and at least be able to get a better view.

both of us thought to head west as that���s where it seem to be going towards, and we were going down a road that had  a wide open view of the sky. we should have at least been able to see the object in the distance, but we drove a few miles and saw nothing but the normal air traffic that is common.
content.summary: 3 lights, consistently spaced, blinking sequentially

content.detailedDescription: I was driving from comanche to dublin and had noticed two planes that seemed odd in that they were flying parallel to each other, about 5 inches at my extended arms length. i continued to watch them to see if they would diverge. they were almost becoming imperceptable to the eye, when suddenly, in the same area of the sky, two huge lights just came on. in comparison to the planes, or whatever the first lights were, these were enormous! it was almost like headlights, yet in the sky. both came on at the same time, and i had long enough to look closely, assure myself they were there and were not glare, and then at the same time both disappeared. they never reappeared, and i continued my drive home in about 15 minutes. i don't see how anyone else on the highway traveling east, as i was, could have missed seeing something so obviously out of the normal.
content.summary: Two huge lights in the night sky

content.detailedDescription:
I am writing to tell you what my wife and i experienced on the night of 12-10-09 in spring hill,tn.

brief account:

it was 10:00pm on 12-10-09 a clear cold night about 18 degrees. i walked outside to retrieve something from my work truck that was parked outside. something caught my attention out of the corner of my eye and i looked to the right and up in the sky almost overhead was this "object" it appeared to be disk shaped,it had several yellowish white lights around it and 1 reddish colored light on top of it. the object moved very,very slow almost appeared to hover at times and the strange thing was it made absolutely no sound.When i say it was silent i mean the light breeze blowing past my ears made more noise than this thing did!
  after watching this "object" for approximately 3 minutes in my driveway i ran inside the house and yelled to my wife to come outside quick! i think there is a ufo hovering outside. my wife then ran outside and stood on the front steps and the both of us watched this object for another minute or so when my wife told me to run in the house and get the camera. i ran inside got my camera out of my camera bag and ran back outside. i turned the camera on to the automatic setting and proceeded to try and get pictures. unfortunately, my hands were shaking so bad i couldn't get the camera to focus on the "object".
  my wife, who appeared to be in shock said i'm going in and looking at it from the upstairs window.The "object" moved from south to north then made a turn to the west after about 1-2 minutes the "object" then made a slight turn and moved to the north(very,very slowly) toward the town center,where i lost sight of it.
  i ran into the house called 911 and told the dispatcher that i didn't have an emergency but needed to talk to someone at the spring hill police department. the lady explained that she was the spring hill police department. i began to tell her what my wife and i saw at approximately 10:00pm moving over my house in the golf view estates subdivision and needed to know if anyone else was calling in to report seeing a strange object in the sky. the dispatcher told me that she hadn't received any calls but would notify her officers and have them take a look.
  i went back outside to see if this "object" possibly came back when i saw a police car coming down my street. i noticed it was my neighbor who lived across the street i went over to talk to him about what my wife and i saw about 30 minutes ago hovering over the street. he looked at me like i was crazy or at the very least had been drinking. i assured him that i hadn't been drinking and don't do drugs and when i went to show him what direction it came from i said "there it is" and we both then witnessed this object (altitude was higher) about 800-1000'. my neighbor looked at me and said what is that? i said i was hoping you could tell me. he said it looks like it could be a military drone as he was an iraq veteran and seen them before. i said a drone? he said yeah, when they fly they make virtually no sound. he also stated that the "object" seemed awful big and was moving to slow to be a drone but was the only explanation he had.
the object then moved off in a westerly direction and appeared to flip up onto it's side as to expose the top of it and accelerated at a high rate of speed and was gone. when i say accelerated i mean if you would have blinked you would have thought it vanished! my neighbor then said i'll be damned and walked into his house without saying another word. i went home and called my brother who lives in new york and told him what was going on.
my brother gave me a phone number to the nuforc and i called the hotline number and talked to a gentleman  who then took my report. the gentleman asked me to call my local news and ask if anyone else saw this "object". i did call channel 2 news and talked to a man named "jim" who told me that he hadn't heard of anything but would call me back if he did. i haven't received a call from him.
on saturday 12-12-09 at 12:30pm i went to the spring hill police station and talked with the lady at the front desk who said she did remember hearing about my call and said that no one else called to report seeing anything. i left the station embarrassed and clueless as to why no one else called to report seeing this "object" it was huge,disk shaped and had lots of lights on it, flew silently and at times appeared to hover over my subdivision....And nobody else saw it?

i am hoping that maybe you have had other similar reports and know what this thing was. was it military? or was it alien? i know what it wasn't, it wasn't an airplane,helicopter,blimp,swamp gas or balloon boy.

please help me...I realize that without video or pictures i'm just another story but would still like to know what we saw on the night of 12-10-09 at 10:00pm. i am puzzled to say the least and have never seen anything like this in my 37 years of life.
content.summary: Disk shaped craft with lots of lights flying very slow almost appeared to hover at times of my subdivision

content.detailedDescription:
Driving east on golf course rd, i observed 3 orange glowing lights off to the southeast over the mesa that sits to the south over mountainair, as i stoped to roll my passenger window down a fourth and then fifth light appeared all in a straight line maybe slight arch to it. then
they started to flicker out one at a time in the order they came on...It was a little after dusk and i could clearly see the line between the sky and the mesa,and they were in the sky...Each one was  easily as big as a house..I must  have been 2 or three miles away from them..It reminded me of the phoenix lights...So i continued out to the highway and started in to town and i saw it again in the same spot in the rear view mirror,but just for a second and just one. then it disapeard..
content.summary: Five orange glowing objects.

content.detailedDescription: My friends and i were taking a walk around my neighborhood looking at christmas lights. we were just acting crazy and were recording videos of eachother when i look up into the sky and just see these 5 bright yellowish cirlces flying across the sky, some moving faster than others. we had no idea what we were seeing because it was nothing we have ever seen before. it couldn't have been airplanes because there was no noise and no flashing lights at all. i didn't think they were meteors or shooting stars because they were going up into the sky, not down, and they didn't look like them what so ever. it only took them alittle over a minute before we lost sight of them.
content.summary: 5 bright yellowish circles

content.detailedDescription:
i was walking through montauk with my family when my mom noticed the object. i looked at it and at first thought they were two ballons. after watching it i noticed they were stationary an about 3/4 to a mile away. i took a picture and thought nothing of it.  about 15 minutes later i looked back and they had not moved!  

 when i returned home i looked closely at the photo.  it appears to have a source of light in the center of each object.  they do not appear to be connected either.

 the reason i took this long to report it is because i had just found out about m.U.F.O.N. a few days ago.

 note: these objects were sighted in montauk near camp hero. camp hero is a state park and visitors are welcome.  camp hero is believed to be retired but 75% is still off limit.  also, the government owns 4 levels under the surface and the state just the surface.
content.summary: Two spheres over montauk.

content.detailedDescription:
Near or around 7:35 pm on 12-14-09 my mother and i were coming back from the town of cedar creek heading toward whiteriver and just across the local landfill there is a clearing and a mountain that is high and rugged. so just as we drive up this hill over the trees i suddely see 2 huge i mean huge lights that i have never seen before and just i notice that there are 2 of them another turns on and joins the the other two that are hovering. at that point there was anther car that had just passed me and it stopped behind me. as i watched my mother notices it and i slow down to stop and i see the mountain side is the color of these objects the kind of color that i have not seen. now all of this happen within 10 seconds. it happen so fast and suddenly that it startled me and my mother. i didn't know what to do so i called our local pd. 
but, this 3 huge ember lights have appeared there before to the best of my knowledge. even our local pd have stated that this wasn't thier first time being called out the the same spot.
content.summary: 3 red orange colored lights over mountian illuminating mountian side

content.detailedDescription:
I was outside letting my dog take a leak and a couple of fields over (i live in the country) a silver disc with a glow (no other lights) landed.  well, it did not touch the ground, it hovered just above the ground.  a platform lowered beneath the ufo and 3 beings walked out.  they did not look like typical grays we all see.  they walked like humans but were smaller. they were too far away to see any details, but it was obvious they were not your typical gray.

my dog was going nuts and wanted to run towards them, but i grabbed his collar and put on the leash.  since it was late and i was just letting the dog take a leak, i did not have a camera or my phone on me.  once i got the dog under control, i ran - fast - back to the house to grab a phone or camera (whatever i could get my hands on first).  by the time i got back outside, there was nothing in the field. nothing!  it was completely gone.  i had my dog with me still and let him off the leash.  he didnt even sense anything anymore.

has anyone else encountered this?

i am a professional employeed person. i do not do drugs, dont smoke and only drink for special occasions. i have never had mental issues and i have never believed in ufos.  never.  but i know what i saw.  i called a friend of mine the next day who believes in this stuff because i knew he would not ridicule me. nobody else in my family knows of this, i fear their reaction.  he told me to come to this site and post my story.

here it is.
content.summary: Saw ufo land and occupants come out

bob dean at project camelot awake and aware conference, los angeles, 19 september 2009 http://www.Youtube.Com/watch?V=phbpgpme3qy presents and comments on some of the suppressed nasa slides of apollo 13, mars, and saturn which he has acquired:

*finally mr. dean shows structures around saturn rings: a mothership some 2 000 miles long "electromagnetic vehicle", and a circular artificial object the size of the moon.

content.detailedDescription:
While driving to work about 5:31am december 14th 2009
after crossing the verazanno narrows bridge from staten island new york to brooklyn to the belt pwky on the ramp that enters the belt pwky from the bridge near the end of the ramp about 500 feet or less from the belt pwky heading towards coney island i clearly saw a white object, round and with a small tail heading toward's coney island, also, parrallel to the roadway and between the roadway and the water, (bay area) about 30 degree's above the horizon and about 1000 yards or less from my position while driving.  
my speed was about 35 mph to 45 mph , duration was about 5 to 10 seconds.
object was about the size of my thumb or slightly larger.

personnal information:
i am bernard mendez mufon f.I. #1038
request you forward the mufon cms case number ,a.S.A.P.
and i would like to a ammend this report  and also put a drawing in the record, but due to me busy schedule ,this will take time. so who ever is assigned this investigation please send me a e-mail and/or give me  call.
content.summary: White flare or orb with a tail possible metor like flare out.

content.detailedDescription:
First i am a pilot and have built and flown a few of my own planes and understand stall speed and what it takes to be airborne.  this craft was in the hovering mode, and going aprox, 35 mph.  altitude could be judged, as it was slightly north and we had the old tower the adjoins the harbor where we were anchored to measure by.

the event started when i came on deck to a completely dark sky other than city lights which were to our east.  i was doing what all sailors do in the night, making patterns in the water. as i looked up towards the east as we were anchored on the fl. bay side, i noted an angled reflection which at first reminded me of geese coming towards the city. i decided right away that this was not a good definition of what i was seeing and realized that something was up there, coming our way.  i called down to my wife to get the binoculars and we both took turns watching the object, or at least what we could see of it.  what we could see was only the angled leading edge facing us and that was only because city light somewhat reflected off the surface which was matt gray and not very reflective.  all of the lower surface was completely stealth and was invisible.  it was only about 1200 feet up and so blanked out a large section of the sky. if i were to hold up a three foot yard stick at arms length, it would have been larger than that, it was massive. the leading edge was rounded and would have been 20 ft. or more high. if you extrapolate what we could see and then carry the shape out, it would have been triangular in shape, but in the stealth mode.  perhaps our military in this case. 

we kept track of it for several minutes after this and it moved over the tower and over our harbor and into fl. bay. as soon as the city lights no longer could reflect, it became invisible, yet it blanked out the stars for a while and then we no longer could follow the movement. no sound was heard, but then there is a constant sound from key largo which never seems to sleep.

this type of craft has been seen about fl. by others as well as other states.
content.summary: Very large, wedge shaped craft over key largo, to fl. bay.

content.detailedDescription:
At approximently 1400-1500 hrs, my wife and i were driving in oakdale, ca., to her sisters. we stopped at a stop sign and i noticed something up in the air. when i looked up at it i first thought it was a plane but then noticed no wings, no tail, no sound, no movement.
i told my wife to look up at the sky and pointed in the direction of the object i had seen, but it had already vanished. this was all done in approx. 2-3 seconds, for as i made my turn it just disappeared. i looked at it for the 2-3 seconds while stopped, but as i looked to make the turn, it vanished.
i am reporting this because of another article, 11-30-09 in california, that gave the very same discription of what i saw.
i was very excited at first, but when i tried to tell some one they just looked at me with eyes glazed over.
i am not sure if this is where i can ask about "missing time"? i had an expierence when i was 8 or 9, where i was in my nieghbor's backyard. he was called into the house, for something i can't recall, and i was sitting in the swing set. i was looking up and the sky and thinking that the clouds and blue sky were really nice with the sunshine of late spring early summer of '58 or '59. i remember looking up at the sky and thinking, "wow, that is really neat!" this was early afternoon. the next thing i remember is standing outside my house, in the flower bed, looking into our living room, with the sun going down and wondering how i got there and why was it getting dark! when i told my mother about it, she thought i had imagined it. nightmares and uneasiness about strange and wierd things have been going on for 50 years now and i would really like to know what happened to me. please, can you help?
content.summary: Saw a silvery, object w/o wings or tail, no sound, in the sky

content.detailedDescription:
My mother was awakened in the wee hours by dogs barking. she looked east out of her bedroom window to see a ufo hovering over the dense pine forest that surrounded us. it was located about 40 yds. from our house where the tree line begain.

[we lived out in the boondocks. (my father was a co-foreman of a gas/petroleum plant(location: +32��� 53' 58.15", -94��� 9' 0.40") that we lived directly next to.  we actually moved from oklahoma to texas for him to take the job. a condition of the job was that our family live directly next to the gas/petroleum plant.)  our address was bivins, tx, though we were rural.]

my mother thought she was seeing things so she went to another window but the ufo was still there.  again, she thought she was seeing things so she went to wash her face.  she returned to the living room window to the same sight, a ufo.  later i asked why she didn't wake anyone.  she said that she thought that the craft would be gone by the time she woke anyone up.

she is a stone cold christian who does not lie.  she is very meek.  she never reported the sighting, so i thought i would report it for her.  she would not mind sharing her story.  she is not ashamed of it or anything.  i can put you in touch with her.

recently, when i went onto google maps' sattelite images trying to locate our old home in the "boonies" and zoomed in as close as possible, i remembered her story.

in addition, the gas/petroleum plant where my father worked and where we lived is blacked out on google maps, i guess to protect these types of sites from terrorists, i guess.  

her story is much more detailed and interesting.
thanks
content.summary: My mother awakened in night and heard dogs barking. looked out window and saw ufo approx 40 yds from house directly hovering over dense pine forest circa 75-77.
